long_desc.thetext:
Everywhere in the controller does this.__addItem(this.__lookup(i)) when invoking the function. That means it is the model index being passed into the __addItem function rather than the lookup index. However in the __addItem function, there is a line 

listItem.setModel(this.getModel().getItem(this.__lookup(index)) ||Â null);

, which uses MODEL index to look up in the look up table AGAIN. It is very wrong. The line should be 

listItem.setModel(this.getModel().getItem(index) || null);
